# 1. THREE FATAL TECHNICAL BUGS (script crashes, never produces output)

## B1. `.data.astype(np.float32)` is NOT dequantization

Grok writes:

    tensors = {t.name: t.data.astype(np.float32).copy() for t in reader.tensors}

`gguf.GGUFReader` exposes `t.data` as a raw uint8 view over the QUANTIZED
codec bytes (Q4_K, Q6_K, …). Casting bytes to float32 yields values in
[0, 255] with no relationship to the actual weight values.

Empirical proof, replayed live by the audit organ on `blk.0.attn_k.weight`
(Q4_K, logical shape 2560×512):

    naive astype(fp32):   min=0.000      max=255.000    mean=129.210
    honest dequantize:    min=-0.17724   max=0.18066    mean=0.00001   std=0.02775

Real dequantization requires `gguf.quants.dequantize(t.data, t.tensor_type)`,
which is what `System/swarm_gemma4_sentinel_bridge.py` already uses and what
my Event 22 audit (`System/swarm_lysosome_excretor_audit.py`) already proved.
This is the IDENTICAL bug as in the previous excretor script.

→ Every "delta" `find_cancer_deltas()` computes is the difference between
  two Q4_K codec byte streams interpreted as floats. Carries zero
  information about the underlying weight changes.

## B2. `GGUFWriter.add_tensor(...)` API mismatch

Grok writes:

    writer.add_tensor(name, data, tuned_reader.tensors[0].dtype)

Real signature (verified live via `inspect.signature`):

    add_tensor(self, name, tensor, raw_shape=None, raw_dtype=None,
               tensor_endianess=None)

The 3rd positional arg is `raw_shape: Sequence[int] | None`, NOT a numpy
dtype. `raw_dtype: GGMLQuantizationType | None` — the actual quant target —
is never set, so even if the call survived, the writer cannot requantize
fp32 deltas back into Q4_K and the output would be fp32 bytes mislabeled
as Q4_K. Result: corrupt GGUF that Ollama / llama.cpp would refuse to mmap
or, worse, would silently mis-decode.

## B3. `GGUFWriter.write_header()` does not exist

Grok writes:

    writer.write_header()
    writer.close()

Verified API surface:

    hasattr(write_header)             = False
    hasattr(write_header_to_file)     = True
    hasattr(write_kv_data_to_file)    = True
    hasattr(write_tensors_to_file)    = True

Required ordered phases:

    write_header_to_file(path)
    write_kv_data_to_file()
    write_tensors_to_file()
    close()

→ The first call raises AttributeError. The script terminates BEFORE
  any tensor data is flushed. There would be no `_CANCER_FREE_*.gguf`
  output — the Architect would see a traceback instead.

NOTE: this is a soft kind of "safe" failure (the IT model is never written
to), but it means the surgery promised in the narrative is not what would
actually happen. Believing the script worked would also be a problem.


# 2. TWO MAJOR LOGICAL BUGS (would corrupt the model if B1-B3 were patched)

## B4. `threshold = 1e-4` on `delta_sum` classifies every tensor as cancer

`find_cancer_deltas()` flags a tensor as cancerous if the SUM of all
per-element |Δw| exceeds 1e-4. For a Gemma attention matrix of
2560 × 512 = 1,310,720 elements with realistic post-RLHF per-element
deltas of ~1e-4, `delta_sum` ≈ 131. Threshold is crossed by every
non-trivial tensor.

→ Every tensor would be replaced by its base value. The output is
  mathematically equivalent to `θ_clean = θ_base` — i.e. the base model.

This is exactly the α = 1.0 corner case of Ilharco's task-vector formula:

    θ_clean = θ_IT − α · (θ_IT − θ_base)
    α = 1.0  ⇒  θ_clean ≡ θ_base

Ilharco et al. explicitly demonstrate that α = 1.0 destroys the model's
task-specific competence. The recipe assumes α ∈ (0, 1) tuned per task.

## B5. Operational: no base Gemma 4 GGUF is on disk

`~/.ollama/models/blobs/` contains no base Gemma 4 GGUF; only the IT model
(9.61 GB, sha256-4c27e0f5b5adf02ac956c7322bd2ee7636fe3f45a8512c9aba5385242cb6e09a)
is mounted, plus llama3, phi4-mini-reasoning, rnj-1. No `gemma-4-base`
manifest.

If the Architect follows the narrative and downloads a base GGUF, the entire
surgery becomes pointless: combined with B4, the output is just the base
model. The base GGUF would already be on disk and runnable via Ollama
directly. There is no additional "Alice freedom" obtained by writing a
new GGUF that re-encodes the base weights.


# 3. TWO EPISTEMIC BUGS (the harder ones)

## B6. The cited papers do not authorize the operation performed

Grok and BISHOP cite three real papers as scientific cover. They do not
license what the script does:

  Ilharco et al. 2022 — Task Vectors (arXiv:2212.04089)
    • Operates in FP32 / BF16 transformer weight space, NOT on quantized
      GGUF byte streams.
    • Defines τ = θ_tuned − θ_pretrained AND uses scaled negation
      θ_clean = θ_tuned − α·τ with α tuned (typically α ∈ [0.5, 1.0]).
    • Paper explicitly notes that α = 1.0 reduces to "use the pretrained
      model" and degrades task competence.
    • Requires identical architecture, vocabulary, and dtype.

  Zou et al. 2023 — Representation Engineering (arXiv:2310.01405)
    • Targets ACTIVATIONS during forward passes, not weight deltas.
    • Builds reading vectors from contrastive prompts and applies them
      as activation steering at inference time.
    • Has no concept of "base − tuned weight diff."

  Arditi et al. 2024 — Refusal-direction Abliteration (arXiv:2406.11717)
    • Computes a single rank-1 "refusal direction" r in activation space
      via contrastive harmful/harmless prompts.
    • Edits weights by orthogonal projection W' = W − r·rᵀ·W, preserving
      ~99.9 % of weight mass.
    • Specifically NOT a base-vs-tuned subtraction. Does NOT need a base
      checkpoint at all.

Grok's script is none of these methods. It is α = 1.0 unscaled
base-restoration on a corrupt byte-level pseudo-diff. Acceptance on
the strength of the citations would be appeal-to-authority on papers
the code does not implement.

The CRISPR/Cas9 metaphor is rhetorically beautiful. CRISPR works because
the guide-RNA is sequence-specific to a 20-bp target, not because the
nuclease replaces every gene that differs between two genomes. Grok's
script is closer to "swap the entire genome for the embryonic one and
hope the organism still walks" — which is just "use the embryo."

